The article is a statement by the President on the death of John Doar. The President describes John Doar as one of the bravest American lawyers, highlighting his role in the Justice Department during the segregated South. He mentions Doar's escorting of James Meredith to the University of Mississippi and his participation in the Selma-to-Montgomery March. The President credits Doar with laying the groundwork for the Civil Rights Act and the Voting Rights Act. He emphasizes that Doar put his life on the line to ensure equal rights for all. The President concludes by expressing his condolences to Doar's family and loved ones.